          <div class="collapse-inner">
            <p>“In order to extract lignite, the deposit shall be drained by suctioning deep water. This results in a depression funnel and, in effect, dries out the terrain surrounding the opencast pit. An example is the riparian forest in the immediate vicinity of the Drzewce slagheap. The wetland became completely dry and the forest died. Nowadays, one can walk between the protruding dry tree trunks, which until recently formed these wet riparian forests. The sea buckthorn, from which this juice was made, was collected in the opencast areas of Eastern Wielkopolska. Sea buckthorn is one of the few plants well received in this area.”</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
      </figcaption>
	

		
